news.title: Tenderer of slum-dwellers' houses can't be lax: Court
news.para: Aishwaryagiri Constructions Limited had challenged the decision of Karnataka Slum Development Board (KSDB) of rejecting the representations submitted by it in September 2021 seeking an extension of time for completing the work awarded to it with regard to the construction of 1,978 houses for slum-dwellers.

news.title: Court calls for panel to see if builder Avinash Bhosale has to be in hospital
news.para: Pune builder Avinash Bhosale, arrested in the Yes Bank loan scam case, has been admitted to St George Hospital since March 2023.

news.title: Court grants bail to ex-Unitech promoters
news.para: ​Additional Sessions Judge Navjeet Budhiraja passed the order on the bail applications of the Chandra brothers against whom the Economic Offences Wing (EOW) of Delhi Police have registered an FIR for cheating, criminal breach of trust and criminal conspiracy.

news.title: Tenancy registrations start as Maharashtra's IT department fixes tech snags
news.para: However, e-registration from developer offices is still on hold due to a problem in authentication and the IT department is working on it to resolve the issue, an official said.

news.title: Real estate rates to increase after Rajasthan housing board raised land prices from January 1
news.para: ​Real estate firms are keeping a close watch on how the new rate chart would impact the rate of undergoing projects of the housing board and would increase the rates of their projects accordingly.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Over 300 fail to start work, have to give back PMAY funds
news.para: The district urban development agency, which gives away grants on behalf of the government, has identified 305 such beneficiaries and have already collected amounts from 190 of them, officials said.

news.title: Maharashtra's registration department warns property seizure of people who fail to pay deficit in stamp duty
news.para: Senior registration officials said on Saturday that they had identified around 2.32 lakh such cases last month and issued notices so that they could pay by March-end. Only 11,700 people have responded to the notices.

news.title: Bengaluru: Delays plague Aryan Golden Arena, leaving hundreds of buyers in limbo
news.para: Despite hefty down payments and sanctioned loans, delays plague Aryan Golden Arena, leaving hundreds of frustrated home buyers in limbo

news.title: Mysuru civic body awaits approval for construction & development plant
news.para: The MCC has submitted a detailed project report to the government for a Rs 15 crore plant under a private-public partnership on a seven-acre plot in Sathagalli.

news.title: HC adjourns hearing on plea against Odisha RERA rules
news.para: The Odisha Real Estate Regulatory Authority (ORERA) had notified the amendment on July 28, 2022 for enhancing the application fees for commercial projects under the ORERA Regulations, 2017.

news.title: Indore: 140 illegal structures razed in Sindhi colony
news.para: IMC’s anti-encroachment team targeted encroachments in Sindhi colony and nearby areas as around 140 illegal structures including 60 sheds and remaining pucca counters were removed during the day-long drive.

news.title: Nagpur: NIT rejects over 43,500 regularisation applications under Gunthewari Act
news.para: So far, NIT has received 95,788 applications. Of these, 81,668 had also submitted relevant documents. January 31 is the last date for submitting applications.

news.title: Mangalam Cement posts profit of Rs 15.9 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Mangalam Cement's revenue from operations was up 2.38 per cent to Rs 439.43 crore during the quarter under review against Rs 429.19 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Tamil Nadu's registration department sets single-day record
news.para: According to senior officials in the registration department, this is the highest ever number of registrations and revenue in a single day in the recent past.

news.title: Ambika Chauhan of Parle buys two flats in South Mumbai for over Rs 47.3 crore
news.para: She has bought these apartments spread over a cumulative space of 6,180 sq ft on the 24th and 25th floor of luxury project Raheja Modern Vivarea on Jacob Circle from the developer K Raheja Corp's residential development arm.

news.title: Elevator maker Kone says 2024 sales could rise slightly
news.para: It said demand in India and Southeast Asia had been strong, helping to offset the impact of weak consumer sentiment in China, which accounts for around a third of sales.

news.title: Evergrande Property Services starts legal proceedings against China Evergrande
news.para: The lawsuits, which also name China Evergrande's other units including Hengda Real Estate, come ahead of a high-profile case on Monday where a judge will decide whether to liquidate the embattled Chinese property developer.

news.title: Home sales in USA rise by most in over three years
news.para: The National Association of Realtors Pending Home Sales index rose 8.3% to 77.3, rebounding from a downwardly revised record-low of 71.4 in November. A poll by Reuters showed economists expected a 1.5% increase.

news.title: NGT gives DDA three months to free land of encroachment at Lado Sarai
news.para: An NGT-appointed joint committee, Delhi Pollution Control Committee and SDM (Saket) had informed the tribunal earlier that some people had occupied land, which included a park, in Lado Sarai and built jhuggis on it.
